The paper discusses the analysis of a single-carrier massive MIMO system for the frequency selective Gaussian multi-user channel, which falls under the category of Information Theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the effect of spatial correlation on the performance of the system, which is related to Networked Systems (cs.NI) and Signal Processing (cs.SI). The paper also proposes better precoding schemes, which is related to Multimedia (cs.MM) and Communication (cs.COM).
